summary:
The Security Council:

Recalling previous resolutions on Sudan, including 2363 (2017), and emphasizing full compliance;

Appreciating the Strategic Review of UNAMID by the African Union and UN;

Reaffirming commitment to Sudan's sovereignty, unity, independence, and territorial integrity;

Determining the situation in Sudan remains a threat to international peace and security;

1. Extends UNAMID's mandate until 13 July 2018;
2. Extends authorisations under Chapter VII to take necessary action as outlined in resolutions 1769 (2007) and 2363 (2017), and urges UNAMID to deter threats;
3. Remains seized of the matter.
